        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 4 at 1:47PM EST by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>The combination of southwesterly winds of 15 to 20 mph, with
gusts to 25 to 35 mph, relative humidity levels between 30 and 35
percent, and dry fuels will lead to increased fire danger across
the central Virginia piedmont, from 11 am to 6 pm. Outdoor
burning is strongly discouraged.

Residents are urged to exercise caution handling any potential
ignition source...including machinery... cigarettes...and matches.
Be sure to properly discard all smoking materials. Any dry grasses
and tree litter that ignite will have the potential to spread
quickly.
</description>
